\begin_inset Formula $a_{0}+a_{1}e+a_{2}e^{2}+a_{3}e^{3}+\cdots$
\end_inset

.
 For example, the anomalous magnetic moment 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{e}$
\end_inset

 of the electron has been computed to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}\left(e^{10}\right)$
\end_inset

 with the result in being in fantastic agreement with experiment 
