\begin_layout Standard
The simplest possible explanation for the observed 
\noun on
BAU
\noun default
 is that it stems from an asymmetry of the initial condition of the universe.
 However a net baryon number 
\begin_inset Formula $B\neq0$
\end_inset

 initial condition for the universe is implausible as a solution to this
 problem for several reasons.
 First, if cosmic inflation is indeed the solution to the horizon, flatness
 and monopole problems in cosmology this requires at least about 60 
\begin_inset Formula $e$
\end_inset

-folds of expansion which would greatly dilute any initial baryon asymmetry.
 Second, if baryon number conservation is violated by any beyond standard
 model (
\noun on
BSM
\noun default
) physics at high energies then any initial 
\begin_inset Formula $B\neq0$
\end_inset

 would be washed out when the universe comes into chemical equilibrium at
 a temperature 
\begin_inset Formula $T\gg T_{EW}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{EW}\sim100\ \mathrm{GeV}$
\end_inset

 is the electroweak scale of the SM.
 Third, the SM itself violates 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 conservation and lepton number 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 conservation through nonperturbative 
\emph on
sphaleron
\emph default
 processes 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Arnold1987"

\end_inset

.
 The only exactly conserved flavour quantum number of the SM is the combination
 
\begin_inset Formula $B-L$
\end_inset

.
 Any initial asymmetry in the orthogonal channel 
\begin_inset Formula $B+L$
\end_inset

 will be washed out by sphaleron processes at 
\begin_inset Formula $T>T_{EW}$
\end_inset

.
 Note that at temperatures 
\begin_inset Formula $T<T_{EW}$
\end_inset

 sphalerons are exponentially suppressed and unobservable, hence this scenario
 is compatible with constraints on unobserved processes like proton decay
 
\begin_inset Formula $p\to e^{+}\gamma$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the BAU cannot be the result of an asymmetric initial condition it must
 be generated dynamically by some new BSM particle physics.
 This is called 
\emph on
