\begin_layout Standard
A 
\emph on
field
\emph default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi:\mathcal{M}\to\mathcal{T}$
\end_inset

 is simply a mapping from a spacetime manifold 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{M}$
\end_inset

 to a field or 
\emph on
target
\emph default
 space 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}$
\end_inset

 assigning to each event in spacetime the value that the field takes at
 that event.
 This thesis focuses on the special case of scalar fields, for which 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}=\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 (later on, when discussing symmetries, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}=\mathbb{R}^{N}$
\end_inset

 for integer 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

).
 This thesis also restricts discussion to flat spacetimes
